==English==
===Noun===
'''altostratus'''
#{{physics}} [[Meteorology]]. A principal medium-level [[cloud]] type in the form of a [[gray]] or [[blue|bluish]] (never white) [[sheet]] or [[layer]] of [[striated]], [[fibrous]], or [[uniform]] appearance. Altostratus very often totally covers the sky, and may, in fact, cover an area of several thousand square miles. The layer has parts thin enough to reveal the position of the sun; and if gaps and [[rift]]s appear, they are irregularly shaped and spaced. (Abbreviated '''A'''s.)

Source: FM 3-6 Field Behavior of NBC Agents.

